WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.491 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.491 --> 00:00:08.982 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.982 --> 00:00:24.208 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.208 --> 00:00:26.250 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to "Beyond Belief,"

00:00:26.250 --> 00:00:27.167 align:middle line:90%
George Noory with you.

00:00:27.167 --> 00:00:29.320 align:middle line:10%
And our special guest
is Clifford Carnicom.

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:32.040 align:middle line:10%
He's the founder and president
of the Carnicom Institute.

00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:34.690 align:middle line:84%
Now, that is a
not-for-profit research

00:00:34.690 --> 00:00:36.490 align:middle line:84%
and educational
organization that

00:00:36.490 --> 00:00:39.715 align:middle line:84%
is devoted to environmental
and health-related issues.

00:00:39.715 --> 00:00:43.300 align:middle line:84%
His professional career
includes advanced research

00:00:43.300 --> 00:00:45.490 align:middle line:84%
and development in the
science of geodesy--

00:00:45.490 --> 00:00:47.380 align:middle line:84%
and we'll tell you
about that in a moment--

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:49.600 align:middle line:84%
with the Department of
Defense under a very

00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:51.400 align:middle line:90%
top secret clearance.

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:54.320 align:middle line:84%
Top secret, so can you
tell us everything?

00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:57.130 align:middle line:84%
>>CLIFFORD CARNICOM: No,
but the general principles

00:00:57.130 --> 00:00:58.570 align:middle line:84%
can come out, one
way or another.

00:00:58.570 --> 00:01:01.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Clifford,
what is geodesy?

00:01:01.210 --> 00:01:04.060 align:middle line:10%
>>CARNICOM: Geodesy is a
science that actually has it's--

00:01:04.060 --> 00:01:05.950 align:middle line:10%
well, it goes back to
the beginning of time.

00:01:05.950 --> 00:01:09.310 align:middle line:10%
But it was developed in
the 1800s more fully.

00:01:09.310 --> 00:01:12.280 align:middle line:10%
And it has to do with
the study of the Earth.

00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:14.810 align:middle line:10%
And it covers three main
fields of the Earth.

00:01:14.810 --> 00:01:16.690 align:middle line:10%
One would be the size
and shape of the earth.

00:01:16.690 --> 00:01:19.660 align:middle line:84%
And that's in a very
detailed, comprehensive,

00:01:19.660 --> 00:01:22.090 align:middle line:84%
three-dimensional
sense, not just a ball.

00:01:22.090 --> 00:01:25.750 align:middle line:84%
And the second would be what we
call satellite geodesy, which

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:28.690 align:middle line:84%
would have to do with all
the dynamics of spacecraft,

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:31.460 align:middle line:84%
and orbital mechanics,
and that type of thing.

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:33.940 align:middle line:84%
And the third part
would be a study

00:01:33.940 --> 00:01:37.600 align:middle line:84%
of the gravitational field,
three-dimensional modeling

00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:39.275 align:middle line:84%
of the gravitational
field of the Earth.

00:01:39.275 --> 00:01:40.650 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
field that I was--

00:01:40.650 --> 00:01:40.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I see.

00:01:40.870 --> 00:01:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: --most involved with
was the gravitational modeling.

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:46.330 align:middle line:84%
So it's basically the
geophysical aspects

00:01:46.330 --> 00:01:48.310 align:middle line:84%
of the Earth as
well as geometric.

00:01:48.310 --> 00:01:51.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What we know of the
planet, and what we're told,

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:52.765 align:middle line:90%
are they two different things?

00:01:52.765 --> 00:01:56.830 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Well, it depends on
what scale you're talking of.

00:01:56.830 --> 00:02:01.270 align:middle line:84%
That's a very physical,
mathematical, astronomical

00:02:01.270 --> 00:02:02.080 align:middle line:90%
science.

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:05.650 align:middle line:84%
So these sciences are
very deeply rooted,

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:08.680 align:middle line:84%
have deeply
conventional history.

00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:10.120 align:middle line:90%
That needs to be understood.

00:02:10.120 --> 00:02:12.250 align:middle line:84%
That's a very
solid, real science.

00:02:12.250 --> 00:02:14.530 align:middle line:84%
This is the background that
I come from is primarily

00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:16.700 align:middle line:90%
a scientific background.

00:02:16.700 --> 00:02:19.360 align:middle line:84%
I am curious about most
everything in the world.

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:22.300 align:middle line:84%
And I understand that the
world is full of mysteries--

00:02:22.300 --> 00:02:23.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, yeah!

00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:24.770 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: --in
many, many ways.

00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:26.230 align:middle line:84%
But I think it's
very important to,

00:02:26.230 --> 00:02:29.560 align:middle line:84%
also, connect with the
history before us and the work

00:02:29.560 --> 00:02:32.050 align:middle line:84%
that people have done
before us, to prepare us,

00:02:32.050 --> 00:02:35.170 align:middle line:84%
along the conventional
lines, so that we're

00:02:35.170 --> 00:02:37.827 align:middle line:84%
able to accept new information
that comes in our time.

00:02:37.827 --> 00:02:39.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What got
you into this field?

00:02:39.410 --> 00:02:41.118 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you don't wake
up as a little boy

00:02:41.118 --> 00:02:43.390 align:middle line:84%
and say, this is what I'm
going to do when I grow up!

00:02:43.390 --> 00:02:45.310 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: When I
first got into school,

00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:46.510 align:middle line:90%
I actually was an art major.

00:02:46.510 --> 00:02:47.677 align:middle line:90%
So my mind is a little bit--

00:02:47.677 --> 00:02:48.477 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:02:48.477 --> 00:02:50.440 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Yeah, my
mind is a little bit,

00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:53.710 align:middle line:84%
let's say, diverse, in
terms of what interests me.

00:02:53.710 --> 00:02:59.562 align:middle line:84%
But I've also always had,
also, an intuitive involvement

00:02:59.562 --> 00:03:01.270 align:middle line:84%
and appeal with the
world of mathematics.

00:03:01.270 --> 00:03:04.240 align:middle line:90%


00:03:04.240 --> 00:03:06.010 align:middle line:90%
It's very pure form to me.

00:03:06.010 --> 00:03:09.100 align:middle line:84%
I think music and
mathematics are

00:03:09.100 --> 00:03:12.400 align:middle line:84%
two of the purest
forms of communication,

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:15.407 align:middle line:84%
I suppose, in the
existence in the cosmos.

00:03:15.407 --> 00:03:16.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I've always
been drawn to that.

00:03:16.990 --> 00:03:20.440 align:middle line:84%
And one makes choices
about their career path.

00:03:20.440 --> 00:03:22.630 align:middle line:84%
And at one point, I
realized the art world

00:03:22.630 --> 00:03:24.550 align:middle line:84%
was going to have
its own complications

00:03:24.550 --> 00:03:28.840 align:middle line:84%
and difficulties of, let's
say, how to make a livelihood.

00:03:28.840 --> 00:03:32.410 align:middle line:84%
So I took my talents
in the hard sciences,

00:03:32.410 --> 00:03:35.150 align:middle line:90%
is what it amounts to.

00:03:35.150 --> 00:03:38.095 align:middle line:84%
But also, because I had an
intuitive appeal to them

00:03:38.095 --> 00:03:38.895 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:03:38.895 --> 00:03:42.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Geoengineering,
which is a phrase

00:03:42.220 --> 00:03:45.315 align:middle line:84%
we hear all the time,
but exactly what is that?

00:03:45.315 --> 00:03:47.530 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Yeah, it's a
phrase that's actually,

00:03:47.530 --> 00:03:52.210 align:middle line:84%
it's been coined to try and
fit a set of circumstances that

00:03:52.210 --> 00:03:54.850 align:middle line:90%
have developed in our lifetime.

00:03:54.850 --> 00:04:01.460 align:middle line:84%
Now, the term has, to me, taken
on a very limited definition

00:04:01.460 --> 00:04:03.470 align:middle line:90%
in the public sphere.

00:04:03.470 --> 00:04:06.110 align:middle line:84%
You can now find
academic programs

00:04:06.110 --> 00:04:08.000 align:middle line:90%
in the field of geoengineering.

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:13.010 align:middle line:84%
It's a fairly new evolution
in terms of science.

00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:16.820 align:middle line:84%
The definition of that field
is highly restrictive, to me,

00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:18.500 align:middle line:84%
and is not reflective
of, really,

00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:22.069 align:middle line:84%
what the totality of that word
means, if we look at a word.

00:04:22.069 --> 00:04:24.400 align:middle line:84%
That definition,
as I understand it,

00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:27.785 align:middle line:84%
as it has propagated through
the academic, and political,

00:04:27.785 --> 00:04:33.980 align:middle line:84%
and media circles, is restricted
to the study of, basically,

00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:35.870 align:middle line:84%
controlling heat
flow into the earth.

00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:39.470 align:middle line:84%
The issue of global warming
and reflecting solar radiation

00:04:39.470 --> 00:04:42.250 align:middle line:84%
is how that word is
classically framed now,

00:04:42.250 --> 00:04:43.510 align:middle line:90%
in all ways to the public.

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:45.830 align:middle line:84%
This is how the
public, I think, is

00:04:45.830 --> 00:04:48.140 align:middle line:90%
intended to perceive that word.

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:51.170 align:middle line:84%
That is not what that word
means to me as I take it

00:04:51.170 --> 00:04:53.960 align:middle line:84%
by its root, root
meaning, as well as

00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:55.810 align:middle line:90%
what I see in my research.

00:04:55.810 --> 00:04:57.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And so what
does it mean to you?

00:04:57.540 --> 00:04:59.330 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Well, you take
those two words together.

00:04:59.330 --> 00:05:01.505 align:middle line:84%
You start with engineering,
and you start with geo,

00:05:01.505 --> 00:05:02.930 align:middle line:90%
and you dissect those.

00:05:02.930 --> 00:05:05.210 align:middle line:84%
Engineering is a
very broad science.

00:05:05.210 --> 00:05:08.270 align:middle line:84%
And in general, in
general, engineering,

00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:10.500 align:middle line:90%
it's the development of systems.

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.650 align:middle line:90%
It's not a specific program.

00:05:12.650 --> 00:05:14.840 align:middle line:90%
It's the development of systems.

00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:17.690 align:middle line:84%
Those systems are
usually very technical.

00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:19.580 align:middle line:90%
They're usually very complex.

00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:22.040 align:middle line:84%
And there is even
the word of savviness

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:24.890 align:middle line:84%
that goes with
engineering, to come up

00:05:24.890 --> 00:05:27.860 align:middle line:84%
with a clever way of
solving a problem.

00:05:27.860 --> 00:05:29.240 align:middle line:90%
This is what makes it unique.

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:32.060 align:middle line:84%
And engineering is
applied to, literally,

00:05:32.060 --> 00:05:35.450 align:middle line:84%
any type of building, any
kind of system that we

00:05:35.450 --> 00:05:36.920 align:middle line:90%
see in our world.

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:39.020 align:middle line:84%
If you now couple that
word with the word

00:05:39.020 --> 00:05:42.710 align:middle line:84%
geo, which means Earth, this
is what that word means.

00:05:42.710 --> 00:05:45.410 align:middle line:84%
This word means,
in my definition--

00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:49.340 align:middle line:84%
this definition is not readily
accepted by the public.

00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:51.980 align:middle line:84%
But it's very real, in
terms of what is happening--

00:05:51.980 --> 00:05:55.130 align:middle line:84%
and that is the
development of systems

00:05:55.130 --> 00:05:58.520 align:middle line:84%
applications through
almost any means

00:05:58.520 --> 00:06:01.790 align:middle line:84%
imaginable, involving
creativity, technology,

00:06:01.790 --> 00:06:07.730 align:middle line:84%
ingenuity, systems of
control, and manipulation,

00:06:07.730 --> 00:06:10.820 align:middle line:84%
applied to the Earth,
the Earth as a whole,

00:06:10.820 --> 00:06:14.790 align:middle line:84%
not a specific single
part of Earth dynamics

00:06:14.790 --> 00:06:18.305 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is this a
good thing for us?

00:06:18.305 --> 00:06:20.020 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: It could
be either, right?

00:06:20.020 --> 00:06:20.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, boy.

00:06:20.820 --> 00:06:22.210 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: It can be either.

00:06:22.210 --> 00:06:23.810 align:middle line:90%
What can we do with technology?

00:06:23.810 --> 00:06:25.540 align:middle line:84%
What can we do with
the human mind?

00:06:25.540 --> 00:06:28.910 align:middle line:84%
We can do whatever our
creativity allows us to do.

00:06:28.910 --> 00:06:32.260 align:middle line:84%
It allows us to be evil,
and it allows us to be good.

00:06:32.260 --> 00:06:37.170 align:middle line:84%
The work that I have become
involved in, and, to me,

00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:39.310 align:middle line:84%
there is no question
that it involves

00:06:39.310 --> 00:06:41.800 align:middle line:84%
the application of exactly
what I'm speaking of,

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:45.260 align:middle line:84%
systems of technology
towards the Earth.

00:06:45.260 --> 00:06:46.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Give me an example.

00:06:46.780 --> 00:06:48.390 align:middle line:90%
Give me an example.

00:06:48.390 --> 00:06:50.770 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: All right,
so weather control

00:06:50.770 --> 00:06:52.315 align:middle line:90%
is one of these, all right?

00:06:52.315 --> 00:06:53.190 align:middle line:90%
I'll go through all--

00:06:53.190 --> 00:06:55.370 align:middle line:84%
I have a list of seven, if
I can remember them all.

00:06:55.370 --> 00:06:56.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All right.

00:06:56.170 --> 00:06:59.200 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: This topic of
geoengineering is generally

00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:03.130 align:middle line:84%
perceived and phrased simply
in the sphere of weather

00:07:03.130 --> 00:07:05.800 align:middle line:84%
and potentially
weather modification,

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:10.295 align:middle line:84%
a soft and diplomatic word,
versus weather control having

00:07:10.295 --> 00:07:11.920 align:middle line:84%
more of a direct
application or even --

00:07:11.920 --> 00:07:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That sounds a
little more evil, doesn't it?

00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:16.020 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: At least
military connotations,

00:07:16.020 --> 00:07:17.830 align:middle line:90%
without any doubt.

00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:20.937 align:middle line:84%
I have a list of seven
areas of application

00:07:20.937 --> 00:07:22.270 align:middle line:90%
that have evolved since my work.

00:07:22.270 --> 00:07:23.608 align:middle line:90%
And that has not changed.

00:07:23.608 --> 00:07:25.900 align:middle line:84%
And we'll see if I can remember
at least a good portion

00:07:25.900 --> 00:07:26.700 align:middle line:90%
of them.

00:07:26.700 --> 00:07:28.930 align:middle line:84%
The first one, first of
all, I call it environmental

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:30.325 align:middle line:90%
control rather than weather.

00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:32.770 align:middle line:84%
Weather is a part of an
environmental control.

00:07:32.770 --> 00:07:36.040 align:middle line:84%
But environmental control means
the entire environment, not

00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:36.840 align:middle line:90%
just weather.

00:07:36.840 --> 00:07:37.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Not just weather.

00:07:37.150 --> 00:07:38.200 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Not
just weather, OK?

00:07:38.200 --> 00:07:39.960 align:middle line:84%
So that's number
one to begin with,

00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:43.990 align:middle line:84%
that already basically
dispels my acceptance

00:07:43.990 --> 00:07:47.350 align:middle line:84%
of that limited definition
that is commonly perceived.

00:07:47.350 --> 00:07:50.112 align:middle line:84%
Second would be
military operations, OK?

00:07:50.112 --> 00:07:52.195 align:middle line:84%
And I'll have to go through
them briefly because--

00:07:52.195 --> 00:07:53.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK, that could be huge.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:55.165 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Every
one of these is huge.

00:07:55.165 --> 00:07:58.880 align:middle line:84%
Every one of-- a third one would
be electromagnetic operations,

00:07:58.880 --> 00:07:59.680 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:07:59.680 --> 00:08:03.100 align:middle line:84%
And each of these is an entire
field of discussion in itself.

00:08:03.100 --> 00:08:07.518 align:middle line:84%
And anything that
I'm speaking of

00:08:07.518 --> 00:08:10.900 align:middle line:84%
is concluded to result
directly from evidence

00:08:10.900 --> 00:08:14.660 align:middle line:84%
that I have acquired and
gained over the years.

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:17.950 align:middle line:84%
Another one would be that
of biological activity, OK?

00:08:17.950 --> 00:08:20.500 align:middle line:90%
And yes, there are--

00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:23.552 align:middle line:84%
it's fair to say, there are
nefarious aspects potential

00:08:23.552 --> 00:08:24.760 align:middle line:90%
within each one of these, OK?

00:08:24.760 --> 00:08:25.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of course.

00:08:25.030 --> 00:08:26.030 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: That's true.

00:08:26.030 --> 00:08:28.090 align:middle line:84%
But the first point is
to be aware of them.

00:08:28.090 --> 00:08:29.470 align:middle line:84%
And then you can
start to examine

00:08:29.470 --> 00:08:31.510 align:middle line:90%
what the applications might be.

00:08:31.510 --> 00:08:33.010 align:middle line:90%
So we're at biological.

00:08:33.010 --> 00:08:36.370 align:middle line:84%
Next would be
surveillance applications.

00:08:36.370 --> 00:08:37.840 align:middle line:84%
There are surveillance
applications

00:08:37.840 --> 00:08:42.443 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the evidence
that's available to us.

00:08:42.443 --> 00:08:45.550 align:middle line:84%
Another would be,
literally, geophysical.

00:08:45.550 --> 00:08:47.230 align:middle line:84%
We talked about
geodesy a little bit

00:08:47.230 --> 00:08:50.620 align:middle line:84%
and how you're dealing with the
scale of the Earth as a whole.

00:08:50.620 --> 00:08:54.010 align:middle line:84%
There are potentially
geophysical applications

00:08:54.010 --> 00:08:56.260 align:middle line:84%
of the technologies
that we're seeing,

00:08:56.260 --> 00:09:00.880 align:middle line:84%
such as tectonics,
this type of thing,

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:03.680 align:middle line:84%
global storm systems,
this type of thing.

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.780 align:middle line:84%
And then the last one is
a little bit more exotic.

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:08.360 align:middle line:84%
And yet it has to be
included in the list.

00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:11.740 align:middle line:84%
And that is since,
basically, our atmosphere

00:09:11.740 --> 00:09:13.030 align:middle line:90%
has been modified.

00:09:13.030 --> 00:09:14.030 align:middle line:90%
We will have to accept--

00:09:14.030 --> 00:09:14.680 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's no
question about in your mind.

00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:17.800 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: There is absolutely
no question about that.

00:09:17.800 --> 00:09:20.170 align:middle line:84%
And within that
atmospheric modification,

00:09:20.170 --> 00:09:23.920 align:middle line:84%
a more sophisticated application
would be what I call--

00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:27.780 align:middle line:84%
I call it the detection of
exotic propulsion systems.

00:09:27.780 --> 00:09:29.590 align:middle line:90%
That's the phrase I use.

00:09:29.590 --> 00:09:33.080 align:middle line:84%
What we're saying there is that
if you have an altered medium,

00:09:33.080 --> 00:09:36.670 align:middle line:84%
and if it's been in an ionic
condition, which we could talk

00:09:36.670 --> 00:09:41.230 align:middle line:84%
about more, is
existing within that,

00:09:41.230 --> 00:09:44.440 align:middle line:84%
changes of the
electrically-charged state

00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:47.110 align:middle line:84%
of that atmosphere
and detection of those

00:09:47.110 --> 00:09:49.915 align:middle line:84%
could be another
interesting application.

00:09:49.915 --> 00:09:51.290 align:middle line:84%
This is a little
bit more exotic.

00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:52.490 align:middle line:90%
The others are fundamental.

00:09:52.490 --> 00:09:54.220 align:middle line:84%
We could talk about
them for hours.

00:09:54.220 --> 00:09:55.720 align:middle line:84%
But nevertheless,
I can certainly

00:09:55.720 --> 00:10:01.390 align:middle line:84%
envision the value of the
ability to detect changes

00:10:01.390 --> 00:10:03.270 align:middle line:90%
in the state of that medium.

00:10:03.270 --> 00:10:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And that could certainly
involve any type of, basically,

00:10:06.490 --> 00:10:09.520 align:middle line:84%
craft of motion, of anything
that we could possibly imagine.

00:10:09.520 --> 00:10:11.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Former
weathercaster Scott Stevens

00:10:11.350 --> 00:10:13.630 align:middle line:90%
was on Gaia's "Open Minds" show.

00:10:13.630 --> 00:10:17.643 align:middle line:84%
And he is a proponent with
you of geoengineering.

00:10:17.643 --> 00:10:19.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: And that
is everyone's pointing--

00:10:19.810 --> 00:10:21.940 align:middle line:90%
all the newscasts and so forth--

00:10:21.940 --> 00:10:23.777 align:middle line:90%
global climate change.

00:10:23.777 --> 00:10:26.110 align:middle line:84%
Global climate change is
responsible for these patterns.

00:10:26.110 --> 00:10:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And there are some insane
patterns, like I mentioned.

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:33.790 align:middle line:84%
However, virtually
none of them talk

00:10:33.790 --> 00:10:39.460 align:middle line:84%
about geoengineering and global
climate change having anything

00:10:39.460 --> 00:10:42.400 align:middle line:84%
to do with quote,
"geoengineering," the less

00:10:42.400 --> 00:10:44.950 align:middle line:90%
polite term, "chemtrailing."

00:10:44.950 --> 00:10:47.540 align:middle line:84%
And you can't have
that conversation.

00:10:47.540 --> 00:10:51.520 align:middle line:10%
No one can talk intelligently
about that phenomena

00:10:51.520 --> 00:10:53.552 align:middle line:10%
unless they address
geoengineering, right?

00:10:53.552 --> 00:10:55.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SCOTT STEVENS: It's
like having an apple pie.

00:10:55.510 --> 00:10:56.860 align:middle line:90%
And that was a great apple pie.

00:10:56.860 --> 00:10:59.447 align:middle line:90%
But there was no apples in it.

00:10:59.447 --> 00:11:00.280 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Exactly.

00:11:00.280 --> 00:11:03.670 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: This key
ingredient, this key factor

00:11:03.670 --> 00:11:05.350 align:middle line:90%
is not being discussed.

00:11:05.350 --> 00:11:08.440 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: Well, even Al Gore
talks about geoengineering,

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:10.570 align:middle line:84%
and its reality,
and the need for it.

00:11:10.570 --> 00:11:14.290 align:middle line:84%
But when it comes to the actual
implications of it happening

00:11:14.290 --> 00:11:18.730 align:middle line:84%
around the globe over thousands
of miles, hundreds of thousands

00:11:18.730 --> 00:11:21.160 align:middle line:84%
of miles of territory,
back and forth,

00:11:21.160 --> 00:11:22.455 align:middle line:90%
no one will talk about it.

00:11:22.455 --> 00:11:24.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that was
our own Regina Meredith

00:11:24.330 --> 00:11:25.930 align:middle line:90%
from Gaia's "Open Minds."

00:11:25.930 --> 00:11:27.340 align:middle line:90%
Pretty interesting, wasn't it?

00:11:27.340 --> 00:11:28.140 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: It is.

00:11:28.140 --> 00:11:30.950 align:middle line:84%
To me, there are three levels
that need to be discussed here.

00:11:30.950 --> 00:11:34.880 align:middle line:84%
One would be there is a formal
acknowledgment of the term

00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:35.680 align:middle line:90%
engineering.

00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:38.320 align:middle line:84%
And like I said, there
are now academic programs.

00:11:38.320 --> 00:11:40.900 align:middle line:84%
And they are restricted to
that very specific sphere

00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:43.930 align:middle line:84%
that I mentioned of
solar radiation control.

00:11:43.930 --> 00:11:46.420 align:middle line:84%
The second context in which
that term is being used

00:11:46.420 --> 00:11:52.180 align:middle line:84%
is what is called geoengineering
in the sense of, call it,

00:11:52.180 --> 00:11:55.150 align:middle line:84%
extreme harsh
pollution in our world

00:11:55.150 --> 00:11:56.560 align:middle line:90%
that we're not talking about.

00:11:56.560 --> 00:11:57.850 align:middle line:90%
That's the second level.

00:11:57.850 --> 00:12:00.130 align:middle line:84%
The third level is
the list of seven

00:12:00.130 --> 00:12:03.025 align:middle line:84%
that I gave you of which no one
is speaking of at that level.

00:12:03.025 --> 00:12:04.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They're afraid to.

00:12:04.150 --> 00:12:06.317 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: They think it
would be an accomplishment

00:12:06.317 --> 00:12:09.160 align:middle line:84%
to speak about geoengineering
in terms of weather control.

00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:10.900 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying the real
world says that we

00:12:10.900 --> 00:12:14.680 align:middle line:84%
have an entire sphere
of a minimum of seven

00:12:14.680 --> 00:12:18.138 align:middle line:84%
major global applications
that everything

00:12:18.138 --> 00:12:19.180 align:middle line:90%
says that they're active.

00:12:19.180 --> 00:12:21.680 align:middle line:84%
This is not
hypothetical whatsoever.

00:12:21.680 --> 00:12:23.980 align:middle line:84%
Everything says that
these are active programs.

00:12:23.980 --> 00:12:27.610 align:middle line:84%
So the discussion, even within
the context presented there,

00:12:27.610 --> 00:12:31.060 align:middle line:84%
is not nearly as broad as
it eventually needs to be.

00:12:31.060 --> 00:12:33.615 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Clifford, do you think
the public would freak out

00:12:33.615 --> 00:12:35.740 align:middle line:84%
if they knew about these
different things that were

00:12:35.740 --> 00:12:37.150 align:middle line:90%
happening with geoengineering?

00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:41.350 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: There
are people that they

00:12:41.350 --> 00:12:43.870 align:middle line:90%
do live a life based in fear.

00:12:43.870 --> 00:12:45.760 align:middle line:90%
I can't speak for others.

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:48.820 align:middle line:84%
I have to follow my
own sense of truth.

00:12:48.820 --> 00:12:51.430 align:middle line:84%
And I have to be
responsible for myself.

00:12:51.430 --> 00:12:54.745 align:middle line:84%
And I attempt to be
responsible in my life.

00:12:54.745 --> 00:12:58.690 align:middle line:84%
I have no desire, no motive
whatsoever to introduce

00:12:58.690 --> 00:13:00.880 align:middle line:90%
sensationalism into this issue.

00:13:00.880 --> 00:13:05.030 align:middle line:84%
I have no motive whatsoever to
introduce fear into this issue.

00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:08.530 align:middle line:84%
I do have the need, and the
desire, and the obligation,

00:13:08.530 --> 00:13:12.100 align:middle line:84%
and the responsibility
to introduce the evidence

00:13:12.100 --> 00:13:13.820 align:middle line:90%
that I know exists.

00:13:13.820 --> 00:13:16.840 align:middle line:84%
My standards are those of what
I regard as a court of law,

00:13:16.840 --> 00:13:19.450 align:middle line:84%
anything that I-- and
also the rules of science.

00:13:19.450 --> 00:13:21.680 align:middle line:84%
I need to be able to
present that evidence.

00:13:21.680 --> 00:13:23.800 align:middle line:84%
We must deal with
the world as it

00:13:23.800 --> 00:13:28.390 align:middle line:84%
is, not as we wish it to be, or
try to ignore things that might

00:13:28.390 --> 00:13:31.000 align:middle line:84%
have an impact because
we are subject to it,

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:33.260 align:middle line:84%
whether we wish to
admit it or not.

00:13:33.260 --> 00:13:35.860 align:middle line:84%
We are subject to
our world around us.

00:13:35.860 --> 00:13:38.560 align:middle line:90%
And we are participants in it.

00:13:38.560 --> 00:13:42.430 align:middle line:84%
So whether or not we're worried
about fear, from my side,

00:13:42.430 --> 00:13:46.060 align:middle line:84%
is irrelevant in the sense
that we must confront the world

00:13:46.060 --> 00:13:47.070 align:middle line:90%
that we live in.

00:13:47.070 --> 00:13:51.160 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, we
are the participants.

00:13:51.160 --> 00:13:53.500 align:middle line:84%
We are the ones that affect
the world, not someone

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:54.670 align:middle line:90%
else directing us.

00:13:54.670 --> 00:13:57.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: This planet,
Cliff, is so huge.

00:13:57.430 --> 00:14:00.740 align:middle line:84%
They actually can
control and manipulate?

00:14:00.740 --> 00:14:01.540 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: Well.

00:14:01.540 --> 00:14:03.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As big
as this planet is?

00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:04.780 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: We
know that the world

00:14:04.780 --> 00:14:08.831 align:middle line:84%
is changing in terms of its
sense of scale in our lives.

00:14:08.831 --> 00:14:09.631 align:middle line:90%
And the world is--

00:14:09.631 --> 00:14:10.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's getting smaller.

00:14:10.480 --> 00:14:13.310 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: (CHUCKLING) Look,
we can say the world's small.

00:14:13.310 --> 00:14:16.880 align:middle line:84%
But we can also look at in
an entirely different way.

00:14:16.880 --> 00:14:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And we're at the point where
every square inch on this world

00:14:20.260 --> 00:14:21.940 align:middle line:90%
is accounted for in some way.

00:14:21.940 --> 00:14:24.820 align:middle line:84%
We're at the place where
every single human being is

00:14:24.820 --> 00:14:27.100 align:middle line:90%
accounted for on this world.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:31.720 align:middle line:84%
So I don't know that I would
accept that it's so small.

00:14:31.720 --> 00:14:34.810 align:middle line:84%
As our understanding
of our place increases,

00:14:34.810 --> 00:14:39.400 align:middle line:84%
we realize we are one small
place in a much bigger place.

00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:45.400 align:middle line:84%
And we need to respect that,
that we are not dominions

00:14:45.400 --> 00:14:47.910 align:middle line:90%
of the entire cosmos, OK?

00:14:47.910 --> 00:14:50.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Synthetic biology
is an important factor

00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:51.520 align:middle line:90%
in all of this.

00:14:51.520 --> 00:14:53.530 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:14:53.530 --> 00:14:56.170 align:middle line:10%
>> 20 years ago,
scientists learned to read

00:14:56.170 --> 00:14:59.800 align:middle line:10%
a creature's entire DNA
sequence, beginning to end.

00:14:59.800 --> 00:15:02.080 align:middle line:10%
A genome, it's called.

00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:05.170 align:middle line:10%
They did this for simple
things, like bacteria, and then

00:15:05.170 --> 00:15:10.870 align:middle line:10%
for more complex flies,
and eventually for humans.

00:15:10.870 --> 00:15:13.810 align:middle line:10%
And then they began to
tinker, to take the glow

00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:18.860 align:middle line:10%
from a jellyfish, and
transfer it to a cat,

00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:22.100 align:middle line:10%
to make critters do what
they'd never done before.

00:15:22.100 --> 00:15:23.950 align:middle line:10%
And as biologists
got better at this,

00:15:23.950 --> 00:15:27.390 align:middle line:10%
says Stanford professor Drew
Endy, a new kind of science

00:15:27.390 --> 00:15:28.190 align:middle line:10%
was born.

00:15:28.190 --> 00:15:30.800 align:middle line:10%
>>DREW ENDY: It's called
synthetic biology.

00:15:30.800 --> 00:15:31.770 align:middle line:10%
It's a means to an end.

00:15:31.770 --> 00:15:35.090 align:middle line:90%


00:15:35.090 --> 00:15:39.190 align:middle line:10%
>> What can we do with the new
tools of synthetic biology?

00:15:39.190 --> 00:15:41.260 align:middle line:10%
Well, we can improve on
what's been spelled out

00:15:41.260 --> 00:15:45.260 align:middle line:10%
over 3 billion
years of evolution.

00:15:45.260 --> 00:15:50.700 align:middle line:10%
We can take it beyond reading
genomes or editing genomes

00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:55.630 align:middle line:10%
and start writing genomes, our
own ideas of what life should

00:15:55.630 --> 00:15:58.750 align:middle line:10%
be like, making
creatures drastically

00:15:58.750 --> 00:16:01.102 align:middle line:10%
different from any
that have ever existed.

00:16:01.102 --> 00:16:02.060 align:middle line:10%
And how do you do that?

00:16:02.060 --> 00:16:04.720 align:middle line:10%
Well, already, one
group of scientists

00:16:04.720 --> 00:16:07.720 align:middle line:10%
have rewritten and rebuilt
the entire instruction

00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:11.980 align:middle line:10%
kit for the very
humble, little yeast.

00:16:11.980 --> 00:16:15.402 align:middle line:10%
And they plan to put their
new recipe into a cell.

00:16:15.402 --> 00:16:17.110 align:middle line:10%
And if everything goes
according to plan,

00:16:17.110 --> 00:16:20.875 align:middle line:10%
it will come alive and begin
making baby yeast, exactly

00:16:20.875 --> 00:16:23.260 align:middle line:10%
like its most unusual parent.

00:16:23.260 --> 00:16:25.650 align:middle line:10%
It will be new in the world.

00:16:25.650 --> 00:16:31.180 align:middle line:90%


00:16:31.180 --> 00:16:35.490 align:middle line:10%
This synthetic yeast will
break the continuous chain

00:16:35.490 --> 00:16:38.970 align:middle line:10%
of evolution that links
every creature back

00:16:38.970 --> 00:16:40.720 align:middle line:10%
to the first living cell.

00:16:40.720 --> 00:16:47.585 align:middle line:10%
It will be discontinuous, in
a way a thing unto itself.

00:16:47.585 --> 00:16:50.340 align:middle line:10%


00:16:50.340 --> 00:16:54.330 align:middle line:10%
And then where do we
take this new technology?

00:16:54.330 --> 00:17:00.860 align:middle line:10%
How far should we or will we go?

00:17:00.860 --> 00:17:03.868 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you think of
that explanation we just saw?

00:17:03.868 --> 00:17:05.410 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: I think
that's, actually,

00:17:05.410 --> 00:17:09.650 align:middle line:84%
a very well presented video
on a very important topic.

00:17:09.650 --> 00:17:15.550 align:middle line:84%
And that subject is that
we are on the threshold

00:17:15.550 --> 00:17:20.710 align:middle line:84%
of a complete change
in terms of our ability

00:17:20.710 --> 00:17:28.220 align:middle line:84%
to interact and manipulate
life and biological processes.

00:17:28.220 --> 00:17:30.160 align:middle line:84%
There is a term called
CRISPR that's come out

00:17:30.160 --> 00:17:31.570 align:middle line:90%
over the last few years.

00:17:31.570 --> 00:17:34.420 align:middle line:84%
And I don't make claims to
be in a genetic scientist.

00:17:34.420 --> 00:17:37.270 align:middle line:84%
But I study enough to know
the general principles.

00:17:37.270 --> 00:17:40.600 align:middle line:84%
And many of us are aware of
the idea of gene splicing

00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:43.030 align:middle line:84%
and modifying,
genetically-modified organisms,

00:17:43.030 --> 00:17:44.000 align:middle line:90%
that type of thing.

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:46.750 align:middle line:90%
But this term CRISPR applies--

00:17:46.750 --> 00:17:49.240 align:middle line:84%
really, the image is
that of a word processor.

00:17:49.240 --> 00:17:52.660 align:middle line:84%
We know what it's like to
take what a word processor is

00:17:52.660 --> 00:17:54.910 align:middle line:84%
compared to our time
on the typewriter,

00:17:54.910 --> 00:17:56.440 align:middle line:84%
and cutting a snip
out of something,

00:17:56.440 --> 00:17:58.780 align:middle line:84%
and moving around, and
making anything you want.

00:17:58.780 --> 00:18:02.160 align:middle line:84%
We are at this point
with genetic ability now.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:05.110 align:middle line:84%
The CRISPR technology
allows for, basically,

00:18:05.110 --> 00:18:07.885 align:middle line:90%
cut and paste of genetic code.

00:18:07.885 --> 00:18:09.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's
kind of dangerous

00:18:09.260 --> 00:18:10.450 align:middle line:90%
though, Clifford, isn't it?

00:18:10.450 --> 00:18:14.260 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: It truly is a brave
new world because the question

00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:15.850 align:middle line:90%
is do we have--

00:18:15.850 --> 00:18:17.530 align:middle line:90%
are we responsible?

00:18:17.530 --> 00:18:20.740 align:middle line:84%
Are we responsible enough to
be able to manage and handle

00:18:20.740 --> 00:18:23.560 align:middle line:84%
that kind of
information properly?

00:18:23.560 --> 00:18:26.775 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, history
says we're not, OK?

00:18:26.775 --> 00:18:27.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's true.

00:18:27.670 --> 00:18:28.885 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: Human beings--

00:18:28.885 --> 00:18:30.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We're not capable.

00:18:30.010 --> 00:18:31.990 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: --can claim
a element of knowledge.

00:18:31.990 --> 00:18:34.300 align:middle line:84%
But they cannot
historically show the level

00:18:34.300 --> 00:18:38.230 align:middle line:84%
of responsibility that goes
along with that to manage that

00:18:38.230 --> 00:18:39.160 align:middle line:90%
information.

00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:42.520 align:middle line:84%
Nuclear weaponry would be a
classic example of this, OK?

00:18:42.520 --> 00:18:45.190 align:middle line:84%
Our environmental damage
would be a classic example.

00:18:45.190 --> 00:18:47.620 align:middle line:84%
These operations that are
taking place in our planet

00:18:47.620 --> 00:18:51.130 align:middle line:84%
right now, which encompass
all seven of those fields,

00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:53.710 align:middle line:90%
they are of the same ilk, OK?

00:18:53.710 --> 00:18:57.421 align:middle line:84%
There is no demonstrated
responsibility

00:18:57.421 --> 00:19:01.465 align:middle line:84%
of our means to understand the
impact of what we're actually

00:19:01.465 --> 00:19:03.340 align:middle line:90%
doing to our planet.

00:19:03.340 --> 00:19:05.060 align:middle line:84%
So I think the video
is very important.

00:19:05.060 --> 00:19:07.750 align:middle line:84%
And it's directly
relevant in my work

00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:11.038 align:middle line:84%
because I mentioned to you
the biological aspect, right?

00:19:11.038 --> 00:19:12.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: As one of those seven.

00:19:12.330 --> 00:19:14.650 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: The
biological aspect is huge.

00:19:14.650 --> 00:19:18.710 align:middle line:84%
It is a very uncomfortable topic
for many of us to speak about.

00:19:18.710 --> 00:19:22.180 align:middle line:84%
But once again, we must confront
the evidence that exists.

00:19:22.180 --> 00:19:24.490 align:middle line:84%
And the evidence
demonstrates that there

00:19:24.490 --> 00:19:31.090 align:middle line:84%
has been the dispersion
of a basically, honestly,

00:19:31.090 --> 00:19:35.620 align:middle line:90%
a new form of life.

00:19:35.620 --> 00:19:38.710 align:middle line:84%
An entire new arena
of microbiology

00:19:38.710 --> 00:19:42.520 align:middle line:84%
has been distributed
upon this planet.

00:19:42.520 --> 00:19:46.390 align:middle line:84%
Or let us say, it has taken
hold on this planet at a level

00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:49.150 align:middle line:84%
that many of us could not
even begin to imagine it.

00:19:49.150 --> 00:19:51.280 align:middle line:90%
It literally exists.

00:19:51.280 --> 00:19:52.150 align:middle line:90%
You could put out--

00:19:52.150 --> 00:19:54.760 align:middle line:84%
I could put out a good
quality air filter,

00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:56.720 align:middle line:84%
probably anyplace
on this planet.

00:19:56.720 --> 00:19:59.560 align:middle line:84%
And I suspect I would be
able to produce evidence

00:19:59.560 --> 00:20:03.430 align:middle line:84%
of a microbial nature
that should astonish us,

00:20:03.430 --> 00:20:07.770 align:middle line:84%
if we actually look
into this field.

00:20:07.770 --> 00:20:10.930 align:middle line:84%
And the behavior,
and characteristics,

00:20:10.930 --> 00:20:15.790 align:middle line:84%
morphology of this
particular microbe

00:20:15.790 --> 00:20:17.740 align:middle line:84%
pose those very
same questions that

00:20:17.740 --> 00:20:22.480 align:middle line:84%
are raised in this video of,
are we dealing, potentially,

00:20:22.480 --> 00:20:26.470 align:middle line:84%
with a synthetic form of life,
or at least something that,

00:20:26.470 --> 00:20:29.950 align:middle line:84%
let's say, crosses the
norms of how biology

00:20:29.950 --> 00:20:32.830 align:middle line:90%
is classified on this planet?

00:20:32.830 --> 00:20:35.000 align:middle line:84%
This is where the
conventional science comes in,

00:20:35.000 --> 00:20:37.655 align:middle line:84%
that we must become familiar
with it, study what that is.

00:20:37.655 --> 00:20:39.280 align:middle line:84%
And in that world,
it's based upon what

00:20:39.280 --> 00:20:42.400 align:middle line:84%
are called domains of life,
that those domains of life

00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:45.070 align:middle line:84%
are determined by
genetic origin.

00:20:45.070 --> 00:20:48.820 align:middle line:84%
You now have to contrast that
against available information

00:20:48.820 --> 00:20:51.370 align:middle line:84%
of a microbial form
that does not seem

00:20:51.370 --> 00:20:54.220 align:middle line:90%
to fit well into that system.

00:20:54.220 --> 00:20:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And that is a
fundamental problem

00:20:55.750 --> 00:20:59.140 align:middle line:84%
when you violate
the basic foundation

00:20:59.140 --> 00:21:03.520 align:middle line:84%
of biological classification
as it is established now.

00:21:03.520 --> 00:21:05.710 align:middle line:84%
It should be raising
all kinds of questions

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:08.950 align:middle line:84%
about, why are we
not investigating?

00:21:08.950 --> 00:21:10.990 align:middle line:84%
Why are we not
taking this to heart

00:21:10.990 --> 00:21:12.430 align:middle line:90%
if the evidence is before us?

00:21:12.430 --> 00:21:14.560 align:middle line:84%
Why are we ignoring
the evidence?

00:21:14.560 --> 00:21:16.600 align:middle line:84%
Why are we not
acknowledging the evidence?

00:21:16.600 --> 00:21:19.010 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm telling
you that it is there.

00:21:19.010 --> 00:21:22.045 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why are we doing
this bioengineering?

00:21:22.045 --> 00:21:25.202 align:middle line:84%
What are we trying
to accomplish here?

00:21:25.202 --> 00:21:27.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: There's always
different directions

00:21:27.160 --> 00:21:29.320 align:middle line:84%
I can take in terms of
an answer to a question.

00:21:29.320 --> 00:21:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And I can't say that any one is
necessarily the single answer.

00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:37.605 align:middle line:84%
One answer, not even an
answer, but one attribute--

00:21:37.605 --> 00:21:39.420 align:middle line:84%
I see human beings
as being really

00:21:39.420 --> 00:21:42.180 align:middle line:84%
a most curious species
as I look at them from--

00:21:42.180 --> 00:21:43.470 align:middle line:90%
I study history too.

00:21:43.470 --> 00:21:46.170 align:middle line:84%
And you look at the
evolution of the human race.

00:21:46.170 --> 00:21:49.950 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that marks the human race

00:21:49.950 --> 00:21:52.350 align:middle line:84%
is that we, basically,
fuss with anything

00:21:52.350 --> 00:21:53.570 align:middle line:90%
we can get our hands on.

00:21:53.570 --> 00:21:55.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And alter
and manipulate.

00:21:55.760 --> 00:21:58.260 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: We will do
anything we can possibly

00:21:58.260 --> 00:21:59.670 align:middle line:90%
imagine is what it amounts to.

00:21:59.670 --> 00:22:01.938 align:middle line:84%
The idea of science fiction,
as I was growing up,

00:22:01.938 --> 00:22:03.480 align:middle line:84%
you have this idea
of science fiction

00:22:03.480 --> 00:22:07.650 align:middle line:84%
as something that's impossible,
something that is removed.

00:22:07.650 --> 00:22:12.150 align:middle line:84%
As I have grown and aged, I
have come to the conclusion

00:22:12.150 --> 00:22:17.015 align:middle line:84%
that if any single human being
can imagine, not necessarily

00:22:17.015 --> 00:22:20.340 align:middle line:84%
even produce,
imagine anything, it

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:24.210 align:middle line:84%
is within the sphere of
consideration and possibility

00:22:24.210 --> 00:22:25.710 align:middle line:90%
of occurring, OK?

00:22:25.710 --> 00:22:28.980 align:middle line:84%
And this applies to anything
and everything we speak of.

00:22:28.980 --> 00:22:32.940 align:middle line:84%
And one of them would certainly
include the desire to control,

00:22:32.940 --> 00:22:36.158 align:middle line:84%
manipulate, and thus even
quote, "create" life.

00:22:36.158 --> 00:22:37.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What could go
wrong in doing that?

00:22:37.950 --> 00:22:38.880 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: Everything.

00:22:38.880 --> 00:22:39.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:22:39.360 --> 00:22:39.975 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: Absolutely.

00:22:39.975 --> 00:22:40.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, boy.

00:22:40.950 --> 00:22:42.780 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Well, it's
just a fact, right?

00:22:42.780 --> 00:22:43.390 align:middle line:90%
Everything.

00:22:43.390 --> 00:22:45.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And has it
gone wrong already,

00:22:45.060 --> 00:22:47.340 align:middle line:90%
and we just don't know about it?

00:22:47.340 --> 00:22:50.730 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: We don't know
enough because, unfortunately, I

00:22:50.730 --> 00:22:55.950 align:middle line:84%
do not have a network of
what I would call dedicated

00:22:55.950 --> 00:22:59.010 align:middle line:84%
professionals willing to commit
themselves to the problems

00:22:59.010 --> 00:23:07.170 align:middle line:84%
before us, to truly assess the
scope and impact of what it is

00:23:07.170 --> 00:23:11.670 align:middle line:84%
that exists before us with
this alteration of life

00:23:11.670 --> 00:23:13.110 align:middle line:90%
on this planet.

00:23:13.110 --> 00:23:15.420 align:middle line:84%
When I'm speaking
of microbial life,

00:23:15.420 --> 00:23:20.010 align:middle line:84%
this microbial life is
affecting our existence, OK?

00:23:20.010 --> 00:23:20.810 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:23:20.810 --> 00:23:23.340 align:middle line:90%
There's no way it can be denied.

00:23:23.340 --> 00:23:24.990 align:middle line:90%
It is affecting our life.

00:23:24.990 --> 00:23:28.080 align:middle line:84%
It's affecting all
life on this planet,

00:23:28.080 --> 00:23:32.370 align:middle line:84%
and how you can let
something sit like that, OK?

00:23:32.370 --> 00:23:35.010 align:middle line:84%
How can you ignore that
evidence which exists?

00:23:35.010 --> 00:23:37.170 align:middle line:84%
Are you even willing to
look at the evidence?

00:23:37.170 --> 00:23:39.900 align:middle line:84%
Because how can you
answer your question

00:23:39.900 --> 00:23:42.360 align:middle line:84%
of what the impact
is unless you even

00:23:42.360 --> 00:23:43.900 align:middle line:90%
know what you're working with?

00:23:43.900 --> 00:23:47.310 align:middle line:84%
And right now, that work is
contained within, basically,

00:23:47.310 --> 00:23:49.800 align:middle line:84%
a set of notebooks that I
have accumulated and developed

00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:52.590 align:middle line:84%
over the last 20 years that
are a record of my work.

00:23:52.590 --> 00:23:56.490 align:middle line:84%
This is the only place that I
know that that problem is being

00:23:56.490 --> 00:24:00.120 align:middle line:84%
addressed correctly,
the best way that I can,

00:24:00.120 --> 00:24:01.860 align:middle line:90%
as a single individual.

00:24:01.860 --> 00:24:05.040 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that I have the
capacity, even the talent,

00:24:05.040 --> 00:24:08.160 align:middle line:84%
and the skill to address the
entire scope of problems that

00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:13.800 align:middle line:84%
is inherent in the claim
of a new form of biology

00:24:13.800 --> 00:24:16.860 align:middle line:84%
on this planet, that
affects all life, including

00:24:16.860 --> 00:24:17.700 align:middle line:90%
the human species?

00:24:17.700 --> 00:24:19.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's
an old saying, it's

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:21.900 align:middle line:84%
not good to play around
with Mother Nature.

00:24:21.900 --> 00:24:23.620 align:middle line:90%
I think that may be true.

00:24:23.620 --> 00:24:27.040 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Well,
let's just say, I can--

00:24:27.040 --> 00:24:30.390 align:middle line:84%
well, you can get off into
spiritual discussions.

00:24:30.390 --> 00:24:32.220 align:middle line:90%
Let's just say, I am in awe.

00:24:32.220 --> 00:24:35.790 align:middle line:84%
I am in awe, throughout
my entire life,

00:24:35.790 --> 00:24:38.820 align:middle line:84%
at the world of nature
around me, entirely in awe.

00:24:38.820 --> 00:24:43.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And by being in awe,
is that what God has given us?

00:24:43.290 --> 00:24:45.270 align:middle line:84%
Or is that what
we have given it?

00:24:45.270 --> 00:24:48.540 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Oh, no, we
are not the gifters.

00:24:48.540 --> 00:24:49.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: At all.

00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:56.100 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: No, no,
we're screaming,

00:24:56.100 --> 00:24:57.615 align:middle line:90%
babbling kids in the crib.

00:24:57.615 --> 00:24:59.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are we playing
around with something

00:24:59.490 --> 00:25:00.720 align:middle line:90%
a little too dangerous.

00:25:00.720 --> 00:25:03.540 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: We are
playing around with things

00:25:03.540 --> 00:25:09.240 align:middle line:84%
that we do not have the
ability to even comprehend

00:25:09.240 --> 00:25:10.410 align:middle line:90%
the full impact.

00:25:10.410 --> 00:25:13.560 align:middle line:84%
We never, never will
have the capacity

00:25:13.560 --> 00:25:17.190 align:middle line:84%
to understand the full
impact of that which

00:25:17.190 --> 00:25:18.720 align:middle line:90%
exists in this universe, never.

00:25:18.720 --> 00:25:20.137 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do
we know, Clifford,

00:25:20.137 --> 00:25:22.860 align:middle line:84%
that this manipulation,
this bioengineering,

00:25:22.860 --> 00:25:25.770 align:middle line:84%
this whatever they're
doing to the planet

00:25:25.770 --> 00:25:30.690 align:middle line:84%
isn't affecting us with some new
diseases, and new things that

00:25:30.690 --> 00:25:31.490 align:middle line:90%
are happening?

00:25:31.490 --> 00:25:32.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: Well, it is.

00:25:32.490 --> 00:25:35.050 align:middle line:90%


00:25:35.050 --> 00:25:36.960 align:middle line:84%
There is a term
called Morgellons.

00:25:36.960 --> 00:25:38.340 align:middle line:90%
I didn't create the term.

00:25:38.340 --> 00:25:42.930 align:middle line:84%
It has come into existence,
and it has a problem.

00:25:42.930 --> 00:25:48.720 align:middle line:84%
The term has a problem in that
if language is not sanctioned

00:25:48.720 --> 00:25:54.060 align:middle line:84%
by those that have the
means to control, basically,

00:25:54.060 --> 00:25:58.740 align:middle line:84%
the structure of
language, basically, then

00:25:58.740 --> 00:26:00.480 align:middle line:90%
the term is not accepted.

00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:04.500 align:middle line:84%
Morgellons is a term that
has evolved to describe

00:26:04.500 --> 00:26:07.140 align:middle line:90%
a new disease in our world, OK?

00:26:07.140 --> 00:26:09.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I started getting
calls years ago on the radio

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:11.730 align:middle line:84%
show "Coast to
Coast" from people

00:26:11.730 --> 00:26:13.440 align:middle line:90%
talking about Morgellons.

00:26:13.440 --> 00:26:15.983 align:middle line:84%
And initially, I'd say,
what the heck is this?

00:26:15.983 --> 00:26:17.400 align:middle line:84%
But then they would
talk about it,

00:26:17.400 --> 00:26:18.983 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to
have you explain what

00:26:18.983 --> 00:26:21.030 align:middle line:90%
this disease apparently is.

00:26:21.030 --> 00:26:22.770 align:middle line:84%
But they were talking
about little fibers

00:26:22.770 --> 00:26:26.460 align:middle line:84%
growing out of their arms, and
feeling like there were insects

00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:28.330 align:middle line:90%
crawling under their skin.

00:26:28.330 --> 00:26:30.060 align:middle line:90%
What the heck is this thing?

00:26:30.060 --> 00:26:33.030 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: The term is
applied to a condition which

00:26:33.030 --> 00:26:33.930 align:middle line:90%
does exist.

00:26:33.930 --> 00:26:35.400 align:middle line:90%
It is real.

00:26:35.400 --> 00:26:39.300 align:middle line:84%
The term, the name was
given by a citizen.

00:26:39.300 --> 00:26:41.700 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, it
is not accepted.

00:26:41.700 --> 00:26:45.660 align:middle line:84%
There is no formal acceptance
of the condition or disease,

00:26:45.660 --> 00:26:47.700 align:middle line:90%
whatever we wish to call it.

00:26:47.700 --> 00:26:51.270 align:middle line:84%
So it exists in
this ambiguous state

00:26:51.270 --> 00:26:53.700 align:middle line:84%
that there's a lot of evidence
to say that it's real.

00:26:53.700 --> 00:26:55.560 align:middle line:84%
And I would go beyond
the point of a lot.

00:26:55.560 --> 00:26:57.720 align:middle line:84%
The evidence is clear
what is happening here.

00:26:57.720 --> 00:26:58.553 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's there.

00:26:58.553 --> 00:26:59.670 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: OK, there is.

00:26:59.670 --> 00:27:03.960 align:middle line:84%
And it ties in directly with
the microbial discoveries

00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:05.140 align:middle line:90%
that I am speaking of--

00:27:05.140 --> 00:27:06.015 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:27:06.015 --> 00:27:08.870 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: --that have
occurred in my research.

00:27:08.870 --> 00:27:11.200 align:middle line:84%
So there is no
formal acceptance.

00:27:11.200 --> 00:27:14.320 align:middle line:90%
And in fact, it's so poorly--

00:27:14.320 --> 00:27:15.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is there a denial?

00:27:15.490 --> 00:27:17.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Oh, it's
more than denial.

00:27:17.340 --> 00:27:19.057 align:middle line:90%
Lives are being destroyed.

00:27:19.057 --> 00:27:20.140 align:middle line:90%
Lives are being destroyed.

00:27:20.140 --> 00:27:22.100 align:middle line:90%
A person will go to a doctor.

00:27:22.100 --> 00:27:23.660 align:middle line:84%
They will show
physical symptoms.

00:27:23.660 --> 00:27:25.960 align:middle line:84%
These symptoms are
quite real, OK?

00:27:25.960 --> 00:27:28.510 align:middle line:90%
We're not imagining.

00:27:28.510 --> 00:27:31.750 align:middle line:84%
I have spent years studying
the so-called filaments

00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:34.355 align:middle line:90%
that we're speaking of, OK?

00:27:34.355 --> 00:27:37.073 align:middle line:84%
I will claim to know
the source of this.

00:27:37.073 --> 00:27:38.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They are
growing out of people.

00:27:38.740 --> 00:27:39.220 align:middle line:90%
It's real.

00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:40.762 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: This is
a real condition.

00:27:40.762 --> 00:27:42.850 align:middle line:84%
It's physical, and the
samples can be produced.

00:27:42.850 --> 00:27:44.380 align:middle line:84%
And I can produce
them in more ways

00:27:44.380 --> 00:27:47.270 align:middle line:84%
than you would
want to know about.

00:27:47.270 --> 00:27:50.140 align:middle line:84%
But the general scenario
that happens over, and over,

00:27:50.140 --> 00:27:53.890 align:middle line:84%
and over is someone seeks
medical help or treatment.

00:27:53.890 --> 00:27:57.610 align:middle line:84%
And the fact is they are
classified as being delusional.

00:27:57.610 --> 00:27:58.660 align:middle line:90%
I have heard many cases.

00:27:58.660 --> 00:28:00.370 align:middle line:90%
And this is the norm.

00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:02.360 align:middle line:90%
This is not the exception.

00:28:02.360 --> 00:28:05.110 align:middle line:84%
There are many cases I've heard
of where they will be presented

00:28:05.110 --> 00:28:06.160 align:middle line:90%
with physical evidence.

00:28:06.160 --> 00:28:07.820 align:middle line:84%
And it simply will
not be accepted.

00:28:07.820 --> 00:28:08.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They won't take it.

00:28:08.290 --> 00:28:10.690 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: There is even
a distance being kept, OK?

00:28:10.690 --> 00:28:12.190 align:middle line:90%
It will not be examined.

00:28:12.190 --> 00:28:15.310 align:middle line:84%
I can show you very simple
things under the microscope.

00:28:15.310 --> 00:28:20.537 align:middle line:84%
There is no, no excuse for not
a direct observation of start

00:28:20.537 --> 00:28:21.370 align:middle line:90%
with the microscope.

00:28:21.370 --> 00:28:23.440 align:middle line:84%
We can go on from there
into all kinds of work.

00:28:23.440 --> 00:28:24.880 align:middle line:90%
But start with the microscope.

00:28:24.880 --> 00:28:26.470 align:middle line:84%
You can not excuse
that, [INAUDIBLE]..

00:28:26.470 --> 00:28:27.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's there.

00:28:27.460 --> 00:28:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: But it is not done.

00:28:29.230 --> 00:28:32.140 align:middle line:84%
And that person--
the history is there,

00:28:32.140 --> 00:28:33.880 align:middle line:84%
for any of us that
wish to look at it.

00:28:33.880 --> 00:28:36.645 align:middle line:84%
These folks are labeled
as being delusional, OK?

00:28:36.645 --> 00:28:37.445 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And kooks.

00:28:37.445 --> 00:28:40.360 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: And they
are suffering, OK?

00:28:40.360 --> 00:28:46.250 align:middle line:84%
And none of us are removed from
this prospect of suffering.

00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:49.600 align:middle line:90%
Many are suffering.

00:28:49.600 --> 00:28:57.240 align:middle line:84%
My small nonprofit has received
well over a dozen offers

00:28:57.240 --> 00:28:59.850 align:middle line:84%
of people trying to
give me their body, OK?

00:28:59.850 --> 00:29:02.585 align:middle line:84%
You have no idea how much
these people are suffering, OK?

00:29:02.585 --> 00:29:03.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're
that frustrated.

00:29:03.960 --> 00:29:07.170 align:middle line:10%
>>CARNICOM: OK, and I have
no capacity whatsoever

00:29:07.170 --> 00:29:08.640 align:middle line:10%
to even begin to address.

00:29:08.640 --> 00:29:10.560 align:middle line:10%
This is a people
offering their body.

00:29:10.560 --> 00:29:14.460 align:middle line:10%
I have hundreds, hundreds
of the suffering.

00:29:14.460 --> 00:29:18.120 align:middle line:90%
You can not imagine, OK?

00:29:18.120 --> 00:29:20.760 align:middle line:90%
We can not excuse ourselves.

00:29:20.760 --> 00:29:24.210 align:middle line:84%
We can not play the
game of language,

00:29:24.210 --> 00:29:27.450 align:middle line:84%
and delusion, and
avoidance, and denial.

00:29:27.450 --> 00:29:30.222 align:middle line:84%
We can not do that and live in
any good conscience whatsoever.

00:29:30.222 --> 00:29:31.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yet we're doing that

00:29:31.430 --> 00:29:33.240 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: And I don't know
when that time is coming.

00:29:33.240 --> 00:29:35.310 align:middle line:84%
But we have no excuse
for it whatsoever.

