That's all in place, OK?

00:39:10.720 --> 00:39:13.640 align:middle line:84%
Thus far, it only exists
within this nonprofit.

00:39:13.640 --> 00:39:16.300 align:middle line:84%
And one of my goals here
will be to see whether or not

00:39:16.300 --> 00:39:18.840 align:middle line:84%
this work can ever be
registered and distribute it

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:21.550 align:middle line:84%
among those that do care,
especially those that

00:39:21.550 --> 00:39:25.480 align:middle line:84%
appreciate the origins
and cause of ill health,

00:39:25.480 --> 00:39:27.190 align:middle line:90%
rather than trying to mask it.

00:39:27.190 --> 00:39:32.470 align:middle line:84%
The second will be that, once
the organism has been cultured

00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:35.860 align:middle line:84%
in a controlled environment,
the next stage of knowledge

00:39:35.860 --> 00:39:39.025 align:middle line:84%
is to try to learn to break
this up into its parts.

00:39:39.025 --> 00:39:42.970 align:middle line:84%
All living creatures are
made of four basic types

00:39:42.970 --> 00:39:46.290 align:middle line:90%
of organic compounds.

00:39:46.290 --> 00:39:49.330 align:middle line:90%
One will be proteins.

00:39:49.330 --> 00:39:52.990 align:middle line:84%
One of them will
be lipids or fats.

00:39:52.990 --> 00:39:54.670 align:middle line:90%
Another will be carbohydrates.

00:39:54.670 --> 00:39:59.080 align:middle line:84%
And another will be nucleic
acids, basically a DNA scene.

00:39:59.080 --> 00:40:02.260 align:middle line:84%
You want to come up with these
things for that way, right?

00:40:02.260 --> 00:40:04.240 align:middle line:84%
You want to come up
with these things

00:40:04.240 --> 00:40:06.640 align:middle line:84%
to progress that knowledge
to the next stage.

00:40:06.640 --> 00:40:10.150 align:middle line:84%
I have done that for
this microbe, OK?

00:40:10.150 --> 00:40:12.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you think
has caused this Morgellons

00:40:12.670 --> 00:40:14.793 align:middle line:90%
disease in people?

00:40:14.793 --> 00:40:16.210 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Well,
it is the result

00:40:16.210 --> 00:40:18.040 align:middle line:90%
of a very specific microbe.

00:40:18.040 --> 00:40:20.890 align:middle line:84%
The answer is it's a
submicron, submicron,

00:40:20.890 --> 00:40:22.840 align:middle line:90%
coccus form, and a bacteria.

00:40:22.840 --> 00:40:25.550 align:middle line:90%
It is very similar--

00:40:25.550 --> 00:40:27.970 align:middle line:84%
it has many attributes
of the bacteria world.

00:40:27.970 --> 00:40:30.460 align:middle line:84%
However, I mentioned
earlier, that it crosses over

00:40:30.460 --> 00:40:31.550 align:middle line:90%
into other domains.

00:40:31.550 --> 00:40:34.180 align:middle line:84%
And there's problems with
a straightforward bacterial

00:40:34.180 --> 00:40:35.890 align:middle line:90%
classification, OK?

00:40:35.890 --> 00:40:40.240 align:middle line:84%
But I will make the claim
that that specific microbe

00:40:40.240 --> 00:40:41.380 align:middle line:90%
is responsible.

00:40:41.380 --> 00:40:43.570 align:middle line:84%
And I will make it
based upon evidence.

00:40:43.570 --> 00:40:47.045 align:middle line:84%
I have 400, basically, research
papers that I will present.

00:40:47.045 --> 00:40:47.920 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's huge.

00:40:47.920 --> 00:40:50.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: If somebody wishes
to examine it, I will say,

00:40:50.740 --> 00:40:53.060 align:middle line:84%
you will have to
look at the evidence.

00:40:53.060 --> 00:40:54.730 align:middle line:84%
You're not allowed--
no one is allowed

00:40:54.730 --> 00:40:56.800 align:middle line:84%
to adopt a position
of skepticism

00:40:56.800 --> 00:40:58.310 align:middle line:90%
until you do the work.

00:40:58.310 --> 00:40:59.960 align:middle line:90%
You have to read the papers.

00:40:59.960 --> 00:41:01.600 align:middle line:84%
And if you have
any doubt about it,

00:41:01.600 --> 00:41:03.350 align:middle line:90%
you have to repeat all the work.

00:41:03.350 --> 00:41:05.860 align:middle line:84%
All the work I've done,
one of the standards

00:41:05.860 --> 00:41:07.210 align:middle line:90%
is that of repeatability.

00:41:07.210 --> 00:41:08.800 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the
rules of science.

00:41:08.800 --> 00:41:10.990 align:middle line:84%
That's a huge task
for 400 papers.

00:41:10.990 --> 00:41:13.330 align:middle line:90%
Essentially, it's all there, OK?

00:41:13.330 --> 00:41:16.330 align:middle line:84%
In addition to the
biomolecules of life,

00:41:16.330 --> 00:41:19.600 align:middle line:84%
the next thing you need, if
you can get it, is the DNA.

00:41:19.600 --> 00:41:22.120 align:middle line:84%
I have the DNA for
this organism, OK?

00:41:22.120 --> 00:41:23.860 align:middle line:84%
I know how to get
it, and I have it.

00:41:23.860 --> 00:41:27.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Was it done
internationally, Clifford?

00:41:27.070 --> 00:41:29.450 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Again, we
don't know the answer.

00:41:29.450 --> 00:41:31.240 align:middle line:84%
How do we know the
answers to that which

00:41:31.240 --> 00:41:33.486 align:middle line:90%
we're not privy to, right?

00:41:33.486 --> 00:41:35.830 align:middle line:84%
We can try to work
to the answers.

00:41:35.830 --> 00:41:36.820 align:middle line:90%
But we don't have them.

00:41:36.820 --> 00:41:41.260 align:middle line:84%
What I can do is present
possibilities, right?

00:41:41.260 --> 00:41:42.620 align:middle line:90%
Where did it come from?

00:41:42.620 --> 00:41:43.490 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:41:43.490 --> 00:41:45.327 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And when?

00:41:45.327 --> 00:41:47.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Possibilities
are, first of all,

00:41:47.160 --> 00:41:51.310 align:middle line:84%
to acknowledge and be aware
that even in and are always

00:41:51.310 --> 00:41:54.180 align:middle line:84%
these claims of how
we know everything,

00:41:54.180 --> 00:41:56.100 align:middle line:84%
in the world of
microbiology, we're

00:41:56.100 --> 00:41:59.100 align:middle line:84%
lucky if we know
a few percentage

00:41:59.100 --> 00:42:01.950 align:middle line:84%
points of the number
of species that

00:42:01.950 --> 00:42:03.270 align:middle line:90%
exist in the microbial world.

00:42:03.270 --> 00:42:05.400 align:middle line:90%
We know nothing, OK?

00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:08.340 align:middle line:84%
So one possibility is we don't
even know that it existed.

00:42:08.340 --> 00:42:09.780 align:middle line:90%
That's one, OK?

00:42:09.780 --> 00:42:12.060 align:middle line:84%
But you'll have to look
at history and chronology.

00:42:12.060 --> 00:42:15.870 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, you have
a onset and an arrival

00:42:15.870 --> 00:42:18.090 align:middle line:84%
of this particular
condition, we're

00:42:18.090 --> 00:42:19.990 align:middle line:90%
talking the last 20, 30 years.

00:42:19.990 --> 00:42:22.390 align:middle line:84%
So we don't have something
that has a history prior

00:42:22.390 --> 00:42:23.190 align:middle line:90%
to what we know of.

00:42:23.190 --> 00:42:24.773 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So what you
can say though is

00:42:24.773 --> 00:42:27.030 align:middle line:84%
you believe Morgellons,
this disease,

00:42:27.030 --> 00:42:28.980 align:middle line:90%
has come from geoengineering.

00:42:28.980 --> 00:42:32.040 align:middle line:84%
But you don't know if
it's intentional or not,

00:42:32.040 --> 00:42:33.000 align:middle line:90%
could be a mistake.

00:42:33.000 --> 00:42:34.375 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: No,
it's intentional.

00:42:34.375 --> 00:42:35.470 align:middle line:90%
We know that much.

00:42:35.470 --> 00:42:36.480 align:middle line:90%
It's by design.

00:42:36.480 --> 00:42:39.010 align:middle line:84%
We know that much
because it's dispersed.

00:42:39.010 --> 00:42:40.650 align:middle line:90%
It's dispersed.

00:42:40.650 --> 00:42:42.915 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What's the intent then?

00:42:42.915 --> 00:42:46.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: The intent is
within those seven fields

00:42:46.160 --> 00:42:47.390 align:middle line:90%
that I mentioned.

00:42:47.390 --> 00:42:49.280 align:middle line:84%
That's a broad
discussion, right?

00:42:49.280 --> 00:42:52.460 align:middle line:84%
But the intent is within
those seven fields.

00:42:52.460 --> 00:42:56.990 align:middle line:84%
We could talk about biology
alone in one of those seven,

00:42:56.990 --> 00:42:58.500 align:middle line:90%
as we're doing in part.

00:42:58.500 --> 00:43:00.920 align:middle line:90%
But if we're saying--

00:43:00.920 --> 00:43:03.770 align:middle line:84%
we talked about the
motive of human beings,

00:43:03.770 --> 00:43:08.540 align:middle line:84%
alone, to want to be able to
manipulate and control things.

00:43:08.540 --> 00:43:11.140 align:middle line:90%
And that includes life.

00:43:11.140 --> 00:43:13.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can you
die from Morgellons?

00:43:13.420 --> 00:43:14.390 align:middle line:90%
