that the mortality rate
is increasing because

00:48:06.190 --> 00:48:10.992 align:middle line:84%
of the impacts of the entire set
of seven arenas of application.

00:48:10.992 --> 00:48:12.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes, all combined.

00:48:12.430 --> 00:48:16.300 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: The mortality rate
upon the planet is increasing.

00:48:16.300 --> 00:48:23.650 align:middle line:84%
The disease state and the
health state is omnipresent.

00:48:23.650 --> 00:48:24.610 align:middle line:90%
It's everywhere.

00:48:24.610 --> 00:48:27.940 align:middle line:84%
Everyone is affected
to some degree.

00:48:27.940 --> 00:48:29.740 align:middle line:90%
You cannot be not affected.

00:48:29.740 --> 00:48:31.160 align:middle line:90%
You breathe, right?

00:48:31.160 --> 00:48:31.960 align:middle line:90%
You breathe.

00:48:31.960 --> 00:48:33.220 align:middle line:90%
I breathe.

00:48:33.220 --> 00:48:36.405 align:middle line:84%
If the air has been
altered, and it has,

00:48:36.405 --> 00:48:41.560 align:middle line:84%
and the nature of the alteration
can be assessed, which it has,

00:48:41.560 --> 00:48:42.790 align:middle line:90%
it is detrimental.

00:48:42.790 --> 00:48:44.800 align:middle line:84%
There is actually
nothing you can put in--

00:48:44.800 --> 00:48:49.270 align:middle line:84%
you talked about, can you
improve upon Mother Nature?

00:48:49.270 --> 00:48:51.220 align:middle line:84%
No, you can't
improve upon the air

00:48:51.220 --> 00:48:54.270 align:middle line:84%
by putting something
into it, OK?

00:48:54.270 --> 00:48:56.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who's doing this to us?

00:48:56.470 --> 00:49:00.490 align:middle line:84%
Is there some sinister
group on this planet?

00:49:00.490 --> 00:49:03.880 align:middle line:84%
Are they being done
by governments?

00:49:03.880 --> 00:49:04.900 align:middle line:90%
Who's behind this?

00:49:04.900 --> 00:49:08.320 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: You know, I had
to wrestle with this question

00:49:08.320 --> 00:49:11.050 align:middle line:84%
fairly recently in a
conference I did in Santa Fe

00:49:11.050 --> 00:49:12.670 align:middle line:90%
earlier this year.

00:49:12.670 --> 00:49:15.420 align:middle line:84%
And this question always
comes up as to who, right?

00:49:15.420 --> 00:49:16.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who?

00:49:16.220 --> 00:49:17.020 align:middle line:90%
Who?

00:49:17.020 --> 00:49:20.770 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: And what I
have come to in terms of--

00:49:20.770 --> 00:49:23.680 align:middle line:84%
I ask the problem,
what is it that you

00:49:23.680 --> 00:49:28.360 align:middle line:84%
need to know in order to be able
to get a handle on a problem?

00:49:28.360 --> 00:49:31.000 align:middle line:84%
And the classic training
was, which is true,

00:49:31.000 --> 00:49:34.175 align:middle line:84%
the classic training
is you need the W's.

00:49:34.175 --> 00:49:37.390 align:middle line:84%
You need who, what, when,
where, and why, right?

00:49:37.390 --> 00:49:40.810 align:middle line:84%
You need these things
in order to understand

00:49:40.810 --> 00:49:41.995 align:middle line:90%
the scope of a situation.

00:49:41.995 --> 00:49:42.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's basic journalism.

00:49:42.640 --> 00:49:44.380 align:middle line:90%
>>CARNICOM: [INAUDIBLE], right?

00:49:44.380 --> 00:49:45.850 align:middle line:84%
So I looked at this
over the years.

00:49:45.850 --> 00:49:48.470 align:middle line:84%
And I've heard this question
over and over and over.

00:49:48.470 --> 00:49:53.110 align:middle line:84%
And I started to go
through all of those W's.

00:49:53.110 --> 00:49:55.560 align:middle line:84%
And I asked myself,
what do we know?

00:49:55.560 --> 00:49:57.790 align:middle line:84%
Do we know anything
about those W's?

00:49:57.790 --> 00:49:59.440 align:middle line:90%
And I went through every one.

00:49:59.440 --> 00:50:01.300 align:middle line:84%
And I have come
to the conclusion

00:50:01.300 --> 00:50:04.780 align:middle line:84%
that we know a fair
amount, a fair amount,

00:50:04.780 --> 00:50:07.990 align:middle line:84%
enough for me to be able to
make certain claims to you

00:50:07.990 --> 00:50:09.820 align:middle line:90%
that I would not make lightly.

00:50:09.820 --> 00:50:14.180 align:middle line:84%
And I can say that all of
those W's, to some degree--

00:50:14.180 --> 00:50:15.890 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying
completely at all.

00:50:15.890 --> 00:50:18.520 align:middle line:84%
But they've been-- they
actually have been addressed

00:50:18.520 --> 00:50:21.010 align:middle line:90%
to some degree except for one.

00:50:21.010 --> 00:50:21.810 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who?

00:50:21.810 --> 00:50:23.725 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: And guess
what the one is, OK?

00:50:23.725 --> 00:50:24.525 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who?

00:50:24.525 --> 00:50:25.325 align:middle line:90%
Who?

00:50:25.325 --> 00:50:27.370 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: And for
those that say, well,

00:50:27.370 --> 00:50:29.820 align:middle line:90%
why would anybody do this?

00:50:29.820 --> 00:50:32.430 align:middle line:84%
I will make the claim
to you that we all

00:50:32.430 --> 00:50:37.080 align:middle line:84%
have the responsibility
to answer that final W,

00:50:37.080 --> 00:50:40.920 align:middle line:84%
and that we, when we
know the who, we will now

00:50:40.920 --> 00:50:43.770 align:middle line:84%
be able to answer certain
questions that have always

00:50:43.770 --> 00:50:48.630 align:middle line:84%
remained inescapable because
it is one of the essentials.

00:50:48.630 --> 00:50:53.220 align:middle line:84%
It is true, what we can say,
is that the who have not

00:50:53.220 --> 00:50:55.680 align:middle line:90%
chosen to reveal themselves.

00:50:55.680 --> 00:50:56.910 align:middle line:90%
This is what we can say.

00:50:56.910 --> 00:50:58.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They don't want to.

00:50:58.320 --> 00:51:01.380 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: The who
has not come forth.

00:51:01.380 --> 00:51:03.310 align:middle line:90%
There is no consent.

00:51:03.310 --> 00:51:06.810 align:middle line:84%
There is no consent to the
changes and alterations that

00:51:06.810 --> 00:51:10.830 align:middle line:84%
are taking place upon the
planet, that involve all seven

00:51:10.830 --> 00:51:11.940 align:middle line:90%
of those arenas.

00:51:11.940 --> 00:51:15.870 align:middle line:90%
They violate basic human rights.

00:51:15.870 --> 00:51:17.946 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Could this be
a rogue organization?

00:51:17.946 --> 00:51:19.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: It could
be anything, OK?

00:51:19.840 --> 00:51:28.180 align:middle line:84%
And again, I try very hard to
not eliminate any possibility

00:51:28.180 --> 00:51:30.070 align:middle line:84%
until you have grounds
to eliminate it.

00:51:30.070 --> 00:51:34.840 align:middle line:84%
And at this point, nothing can
be eliminated in terms of what

00:51:34.840 --> 00:51:41.290 align:middle line:84%
who really means and what the
scale of that who really means.

00:51:41.290 --> 00:51:45.370 align:middle line:84%
You can come up with some
strategic answers that

00:51:45.370 --> 00:51:48.040 align:middle line:84%
address a portion of
how things can work

00:51:48.040 --> 00:51:49.840 align:middle line:90%
in terms of power structures.

00:51:49.840 --> 00:51:54.250 align:middle line:84%
But you can not truly address it
when someone operates-- or call

00:51:54.250 --> 00:51:56.740 align:middle line:84%
it even a someone--
again, you, one,

00:51:56.740 --> 00:51:58.790 align:middle line:84%
must be careful to
make assumptions.

00:51:58.790 --> 00:52:04.030 align:middle line:84%
But whatever the who is, until
you know that, you are not

00:52:04.030 --> 00:52:07.720 align:middle line:84%
in a position to be answering
the very questions that you're

00:52:07.720 --> 00:52:10.360 align:middle line:84%
asking about the
unknowns, right?

00:52:10.360 --> 00:52:12.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Based on your
research, would you

00:52:12.580 --> 00:52:14.680 align:middle line:84%
say that the Morgellons
aspect of all

00:52:14.680 --> 00:52:17.120 align:middle line:84%
of this that we've
talked about today

00:52:17.120 --> 00:52:19.990 align:middle line:90%
may be the worst of everything?

00:52:19.990 --> 00:52:22.568 align:middle line:84%
Or is there something
else out there?

00:52:22.568 --> 00:52:24.110 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: I had
to make a decision.

00:52:24.110 --> 00:52:25.490 align:middle line:90%
My work has its origins--

00:52:25.490 --> 00:52:27.440 align:middle line:90%
roughly 20 years of work now.

00:52:27.440 --> 00:52:32.240 align:middle line:84%
My work has its origins in
the geoengineering aspects,

00:52:32.240 --> 00:52:35.120 align:middle line:84%
primarily, primarily,
but not exclusively,

00:52:35.120 --> 00:52:38.510 align:middle line:84%
but what was being done
physically to alter our planet.

00:52:38.510 --> 00:52:41.510 align:middle line:84%
Out of that work
evolved this work

00:52:41.510 --> 00:52:46.600 align:middle line:84%
into the biological
aspect more strongly, OK?

00:52:46.600 --> 00:52:50.740 align:middle line:84%
I actually reached a junction
point in my research,

00:52:50.740 --> 00:52:52.930 align:middle line:90%
where I only have so much time.

00:52:52.930 --> 00:52:55.930 align:middle line:84%
I have to make choices
about priorities.

00:52:55.930 --> 00:52:59.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's true that I
shifted the focus of my work

00:52:59.830 --> 00:53:02.870 align:middle line:90%
into the biological aspects, OK?

00:53:02.870 --> 00:53:07.780 align:middle line:84%
And I did that because of,
really, a couple reasons.

00:53:07.780 --> 00:53:12.190 align:middle line:84%
You could say in a sense an
act of desperation because we

00:53:12.190 --> 00:53:13.270 align:middle line:90%
don't have infinite time.

00:53:13.270 --> 00:53:15.730 align:middle line:84%
I certainly don't
have infinite time.

00:53:15.730 --> 00:53:19.150 align:middle line:84%
But I realize, in terms of
how the human mind works,

00:53:19.150 --> 00:53:21.502 align:middle line:84%
and they're actually
very egocentric.

00:53:21.502 --> 00:53:22.960 align:middle line:84%
Most people think
about themselves.

00:53:22.960 --> 00:53:25.870 align:middle line:84%
They do not think about
all life on this planet

00:53:25.870 --> 00:53:27.767 align:middle line:84%
as a regular part
of their life, OK?

00:53:27.767 --> 00:53:29.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're
into their own thing.

00:53:29.350 --> 00:53:32.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: In general,
humans are very self-centered.

00:53:32.230 --> 00:53:36.640 align:middle line:84%
And so I had to ask myself,
in the time that I have,

00:53:36.640 --> 00:53:38.830 align:middle line:84%
what is the greatest
good, what is

00:53:38.830 --> 00:53:43.000 align:middle line:84%
the greatest benefit that I can
bring to light at this point?

00:53:43.000 --> 00:53:47.440 align:middle line:84%
Because I know, from my own
experience, that when I'm sick,

00:53:47.440 --> 00:53:49.650 align:middle line:90%
I can't fight.

00:53:49.650 --> 00:53:53.940 align:middle line:84%
When I'm sick, I can
not be the human being

00:53:53.940 --> 00:53:56.580 align:middle line:90%
that I know is my life.

00:53:56.580 --> 00:54:00.420 align:middle line:84%
And I see that as a decision
for all of humanity,

00:54:00.420 --> 00:54:04.020 align:middle line:84%
that we cannot fight
if we are not healthy,

00:54:04.020 --> 00:54:06.170 align:middle line:90%
if we are not of sound mind.

00:54:06.170 --> 00:54:10.560 align:middle line:84%
We don't even have the
ability to even, necessarily,

00:54:10.560 --> 00:54:15.000 align:middle line:84%
know what to do if we're
debilitized in some way,

00:54:15.000 --> 00:54:18.730 align:middle line:84%
and hurt in some kind
of way, debilitated.

00:54:18.730 --> 00:54:19.530 align:middle line:90%
We can't.

00:54:19.530 --> 00:54:20.520 align:middle line:90%
We can't.

00:54:20.520 --> 00:54:25.500 align:middle line:84%
So I think that it
was necessary to shift

00:54:25.500 --> 00:54:28.890 align:middle line:84%
my focus so that we could fight
because we do need to fight.

00:54:28.890 --> 00:54:30.930 align:middle line:84%
We need to fight
for what is right.

00:54:30.930 --> 00:54:35.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you join the
great hereafter, who picks up

00:54:35.580 --> 00:54:37.260 align:middle line:90%
this torch and runs with it?

00:54:37.260 --> 00:54:41.670 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: It's one
of the greatest issues

00:54:41.670 --> 00:54:44.060 align:middle line:90%
that I'm wrestling with.

00:54:44.060 --> 00:54:45.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm not 26 anymore.

00:54:45.900 --> 00:54:46.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm not 46.

00:54:46.980 --> 00:54:49.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm 66, soon to be 67.

00:54:49.110 --> 00:54:54.770 align:middle line:84%
So I, through my whole
life, when I was 25,

00:54:54.770 --> 00:54:57.860 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking of what it
would be like to be 67.

00:54:57.860 --> 00:55:00.810 align:middle line:84%
So I am quite aware of this
problem and this issue.

00:55:00.810 --> 00:55:05.270 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying to work on it
quite diligently, actually.

00:55:05.270 --> 00:55:08.570 align:middle line:84%
And I have to say that
the work I've done

00:55:08.570 --> 00:55:11.000 align:middle line:84%
as an individual in
a small nonprofit,

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:13.450 align:middle line:84%
it's actually
mature, as far as I

00:55:13.450 --> 00:55:16.490 align:middle line:84%
am able to-- those are some very
significant accomplishments,

00:55:16.490 --> 00:55:19.790 align:middle line:84%
I feel and think,
in terms of what's

00:55:19.790 --> 00:55:24.230 align:middle line:84%
available to the scientific
community and health

00:55:24.230 --> 00:55:25.670 align:middle line:90%
communities to progress with.

00:55:25.670 --> 00:55:29.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think I have a good
sense of what needs to be done.

00:55:29.420 --> 00:55:33.440 align:middle line:84%
It's very logical to me what you
do next with the information.

00:55:33.440 --> 00:55:36.060 align:middle line:84%
I will never have the
resources to do that.

00:55:36.060 --> 00:55:42.560 align:middle line:84%
So it's fair to say that it's
time for me to consolidate

00:55:42.560 --> 00:55:43.640 align:middle line:90%
the work that I've done.

00:55:43.640 --> 00:55:47.540 align:middle line:84%
And this is a phase that I'm
entering in, this attempt

00:55:47.540 --> 00:55:49.460 align:middle line:90%
to consolidate the work.

00:55:49.460 --> 00:55:52.520 align:middle line:84%
And I've actually already
seen the transition

00:55:52.520 --> 00:55:54.060 align:middle line:90%
of generations and the issue.

00:55:54.060 --> 00:55:54.890 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is that a good thing?

00:55:54.890 --> 00:55:56.390 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: You
have a 20-year-old--

00:55:56.390 --> 00:55:58.018 align:middle line:84%
you have a 20-year-old
kid right now?

00:55:58.018 --> 00:56:00.560 align:middle line:84%
When you ask them what's normal,
it's a fascinating question.

00:56:00.560 --> 00:56:01.520 align:middle line:90%
What's normal?

00:56:01.520 --> 00:56:03.103 align:middle line:84%
What's normal is
what they've grown up

00:56:03.103 --> 00:56:04.430 align:middle line:90%
with for 20 years, right?

00:56:04.430 --> 00:56:06.860 align:middle line:84%
So this is what's
normal to them.

00:56:06.860 --> 00:56:09.200 align:middle line:84%
I know that it's
not my norm when

00:56:09.200 --> 00:56:11.120 align:middle line:84%
I grew up, the
alterations in our world.

00:56:11.120 --> 00:56:12.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you
hopeful for the future?

00:56:12.950 --> 00:56:15.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Oh,
I'm always hopeful.

00:56:15.740 --> 00:56:18.380 align:middle line:90%
I'm always hopeful.

00:56:18.380 --> 00:56:20.360 align:middle line:84%
As long as we know
the difference

00:56:20.360 --> 00:56:24.303 align:middle line:84%
between right and wrong, I
can be hopeful eternally.

00:56:24.303 --> 00:56:26.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Clifford, if people
want more information on what

00:56:26.720 --> 00:56:29.390 align:middle line:90%
you do, how can they find you?

00:56:29.390 --> 00:56:32.003 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: The Institute
does exist on the web.

00:56:32.003 --> 00:56:33.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm here in person with you.

00:56:33.170 --> 00:56:35.000 align:middle line:90%
And I thank you for that.

00:56:35.000 --> 00:56:39.100 align:middle line:84%
But there's a library
of research on the web.

00:56:39.100 --> 00:56:41.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Spell out
your Institute for us.

00:56:41.020 --> 00:56:42.920 align:middle line:10%
>>CARNICOM:
carnicominstitute.org

00:56:42.920 --> 00:56:43.910 align:middle line:10%
is the name of it.

00:56:43.910 --> 00:56:48.140 align:middle line:10%
My last name is Carnicom,
C-A-R-N-I-C-O-M,

00:56:48.140 --> 00:56:50.450 align:middle line:10%
and then the word Institute.org.

00:56:50.450 --> 00:56:51.920 align:middle line:10%
I will emphasize .org.

00:56:51.920 --> 00:56:55.940 align:middle line:10%
The .com is a troll site,
carnicominstitute.org.

00:56:55.940 --> 00:56:57.140 align:middle line:90%
And there's an email there.

00:56:57.140 --> 00:56:59.990 align:middle line:84%
You could send it to anything,
but info@carnicominstitute.org

00:56:59.990 --> 00:57:00.790 align:middle line:90%
will work.

00:57:00.790 --> 00:57:02.480 align:middle line:90%
We're a small organization.

00:57:02.480 --> 00:57:05.270 align:middle line:84%
Like I say, I'm planning
our period of consolidation

00:57:05.270 --> 00:57:06.785 align:middle line:90%
and protection of the work.

00:57:06.785 --> 00:57:07.980 align:middle line:90%
And I'm looking ahead.

00:57:07.980 --> 00:57:10.510 align:middle line:84%
I also have a major
proposal in place,

00:57:10.510 --> 00:57:12.260 align:middle line:84%
whether or not it will
ever be acted upon.

00:57:12.260 --> 00:57:13.060 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:57:13.060 --> 00:57:15.140 align:middle line:84%
But I am essentially
appealing to the world.

00:57:15.140 --> 00:57:17.450 align:middle line:84%
I am appealing to
philanthropy at this stage.

00:57:17.450 --> 00:57:19.970 align:middle line:84%
I have certain ethical
boundaries and guidelines

00:57:19.970 --> 00:57:21.950 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what I
think needs to happen.

00:57:21.950 --> 00:57:24.290 align:middle line:84%
The public interest
does need to be served.

00:57:24.290 --> 00:57:28.220 align:middle line:84%
So I am working on protecting
the work when I'm not here.

00:57:28.220 --> 00:57:30.980 align:middle line:84%
And my job is to
make it available

00:57:30.980 --> 00:57:33.060 align:middle line:84%
for future generations
at this stage.

00:57:33.060 --> 00:57:35.960 align:middle line:84%
And if anyone does wish to act
on the proposals I've made,

00:57:35.960 --> 00:57:38.710 align:middle line:84%
which are listed on the site,
I will become very engaged

00:57:38.710 --> 00:57:39.510 align:middle line:90%
in that process.

00:57:39.510 --> 00:57:41.302 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Super, Clifford,
thanks for having

00:57:41.302 --> 00:57:42.470 align:middle line:90%
the guts to come forward.

00:57:42.470 --> 00:57:43.640 align:middle line:84%
>>CARNICOM: Thank you
very much, George.

00:57:43.640 --> 00:57:44.730 align:middle line:90%
I appreciate it as always.

00:57:44.730 --> 00:57:48.240 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Geoengineering,
bioengineering, it's happening.

00:57:48.240 --> 00:57:50.630 align:middle line:90%
The big question is why?

00:57:50.630 --> 00:57:52.490 align:middle line:84%
We'll keep looking
for that answer.

00:57:52.490 --> 00:57:53.390 align:middle line:90%
I'm George Noory.

00:57:53.390 --> 00:57:55.250 align:middle line:84%
Thanks for watching
"Beyond Belief."

